Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper investigates the degrees of freedom (DoF) of full-duplex cellular networks, which is a fundamental concept in information theory. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with cellular networks, which is a subfield of networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.COMM (Communication and Networking) - The paper discusses the communication aspects of full-duplex cellular networks with reconfigurable antennas. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper involves the study of systems and control in the context of full-duplex cellular networks. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper may involve multimedia aspects such as video and audio transmission in full-duplex cellular networks.
